+**Catalog (`lib/catalog/`):**
+- `classes.ts` — 8 classes with primary attribute and resource type
+- `slots.ts` — 13 item slots with cluster and class-availability metadata
+- `affixes.ts` — 136 affix definitions: universal armor/jewelry/weapon affixes + class-specific skill-rank affixes for all 8 classes
+- `aspects.ts` — 70 legendary aspect definitions across all classes + generic
+- `skills.ts` — 140+ skill definitions across all 8 classes
+- `index.ts` — lookup helpers: `getAffixDef`, `getAffixesForSlot`, `getAspectDef`, `getAspectsForClass`, etc.
+
+**Persistence (`lib/persistence/index.ts`):**
+- File-based via Next.js Route Handlers.
+- One file per entity: `data/characters/<id>.json`, `data/builds/<id>.json`.
+- Git-friendly layout; files diff cleanly on updates.
+
+**API routes:**
+- `GET/POST /api/characters` — list and create characters
+- `GET/PUT/DELETE /api/characters/[id]` — read, update, delete a character
+- `GET/POST /api/builds` — list and create builds (supports `?characterId=` filter)
+- `GET/PUT/DELETE /api/builds/[id]` — read, update, delete a build
+
+**Validation (`lib/validation/index.ts`):**
+- Field-level validators for all user-input values (names, levels, affix rolls, skill ranks, etc.)
+- Affix values are validated against the catalog min/max range.
+- Validation errors are inline at the edited field per `docs/visual-spec.md §9.14`.
+
+**Command palette (cmd-K):**
+- Functional (not a stub): navigates to characters/demo, creates new characters, lists saved characters and builds, exports all data as JSON.
+
+## Data Model Authority
+
+`lib/types/index.ts` is the **canonical type source for v2+**. All subsequent commissions (v3 API import, the scoring engine, comparison logic) must consume these types. The data model explicitly accommodates scoring engine inputs: class, level, per-slot equipped items with rolled affix values, per-slot target specs, aspects with rolled values, paragon allocation across boards/glyphs, skills with ranks, and playstyle constraints.
 
